Iavan Pijoos, News24Two of the men arrested after the truck heist in Boksburg. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Two security guards were shot when armed robbers hijacked a truck on the R21 in Boksburg, on the East Rand, on Wednesday, Gauteng police said.&nbsp;Three armed men stopped a truck transporting cellphones at the Griffiths Road bridge, Captain Kay Makhubela said.&nbsp;Armed security guards were escorting the truck.A shootout ensued and two of the guards were wounded. The robbers left the scene with the truck.&nbsp;It was recovered in Boksburg later and the three alleged hijackers were arrested.Emer-G-Med spokesperson Max Cohen said the two officers were taken to hospital with moderate to serious gunshot wounds.&nbsp;The three are expected to appear in the Boksburg North Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Friday.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.